parse: Personal / Possessive Pronoun - Genitive Feminine 3rd Person Singular
str2: He, she, it, they, them, same. From the particle au; the reflexive pronoun self, used of the third person, and of the other persons.
From pule; a gate-way, door-way of a building or city; by implication, a portal or vestibule.

parse: Verb - Aorist Subjunctive Passive - 3rd Person Plural
str2: To shut, shut up. A primary verb; to close.

word: at the end of the day,
str2: A day, the period from sunrise to sunset.
For. A primary particle; properly, assigning a reason.

parse: Verb - Future Indicative Middle - 3rd Person Singular
str2: I am, exist. The first person singular present indicative; a prolonged form of a primary and defective verb; I exist.
No, not. Also ouk, and ouch a primary word; the absolute negative adverb; no or not.
The night, night-time. A primary word; 'night'.
(a) there, yonder, in that place, (b) thither, there. Of uncertain affinity; there; by extension, thither.
